{This is the first dream position that you should have in mind when playing
against an IQP. In order to win, Black should create a second weakness.
Additionally, the second weakness should be far away from the d4-pawn.
Therefore, the perfect target would be the h2-pawn. Black should start gaining
space on the kingside by means of ...f7-f5, ...g7-g5-g4, and ...h7-h5-h4-h3,
fixing the h3-pawn. Then Black is winning by combining the attack against the
2 weaknesses. The perfect execution of this plan can be seen in the game
Belavenets - Rauzer. Obviously, with a very precise play, White should be able
to hold this position.}  *

