{The side playing against an isolated pawn should try to achieve an endgame
with heavy pieces. Let's take a look at this position. White does not have a
satisfactory defence against the advance ...e6-e5. Even the advance f2-f4 does
not help. Besides weakening the king, this move does not prevent the idea ...
f7-f6 followed by ...e6-e5. Black's plan in this type of position is very well
illustrated by the model game Kortschnoj, V - Karpov, A.}  *

