100,102,89,103,99,97,103,89,88,96,86,81,103,123,149,154,189,185,248,255,273,
267,260,259,249,246,244,262,344,352] The next three examples feature positions
with isolated pawn against c-pawn. This structure can arise in the system 1.d4
d5 2.c4 dxc4 3.e3 e5. Even though Black can play 3...Nf6 4.Bxc4 e6 followed by
...c7-c5, I have decided to include this material in order to improve your
general IQP understanding. The isolated d-pawn versus c-pawn.} 1. d4 ({The
same position with isolated d4-pawn which occurred in the game arises also in
Russian Game (Petrov Defence) after moves} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4.
Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 d5 6. Bd3 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. c4 Nf6 9. Nc3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Nbd7 (
10... c6) 11. h3 ({about} 11. Re1 {see the variation 2...dxc4 3.e3}) 11... Nb6
12. Bb3 c6) 1... d5 2. c4 c6 ({Another way to obtain mentioned above pawn
