1982/(35)} Qb4) (18. Rad1 Qf6) 18... Qf6 $140 19. Qd3 $5 Nb4 20. Qg3 Bxb3 21.
Ne4 Qe7 22. Qxb3 Ncd5 23. a3 Na6 24. Nc3 $14) 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Ne4 {[%cal
Ge4c5]} f6 17. Nf3 Qf7 $6 ({Better was} 17... Rfe8 18. Nc5 b6 19. Nxe6 Nxe6 20.
Qd3 $140 g6) 18. Nd6 Qh5 19. Re4 $1 ({Dangerous looks} 19. Nxb7 $6 Nf4 {
[%cal Gf4h3,Ge6h3]} 20. Bb3 Ncd5 {[%cal Ge6h3,Gf4h3]}) 19... g5 20. Bb3 $5 (20.
Nxb7 Nf4 $13) 20... Rab8 21. Qe2 Bf7 22. Nxf7 Rxf7 23. Re1 Kg7 $2 {This
mistake leads to the loss of material.} 24. Bxd5 $1 Nxd5 {Allows to exploit
the opposition between queens.} ({But also bad was} 24... cxd5 25. Re7 Rbf8
$140 26. Qc2 Na6 27. Qb3) 25. Nxg5 $1 Qxe2 26. Ne6+ Kh8 27. R1xe2 Rg8 28. g3 f5
29. Re5 f4 30. g4 Nb4 31. a3 Nd3 32. R5e4 h5 33. f3 hxg4 34. hxg4 Rg6 35. Rd2
