1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Qc2 Bd6 7. Be2 ({To the
game position transposes} 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O dxc4 9. Bxc4) 7... O-O 8. O-O dxc4
9. Bxc4 e5 ({More popular alternative is} 9... b5 10. Be2 Bb7) 10. h3 {White
wants to keep his light-squared bishop on the a2-g8 diagonal and therefore
prevents possible manoeuvre Bc8-g4 after the exchange on d4 with Nb6 to follow.
} exd4 ({After} 10... Qe7 {White continues with} 11. Bb3 h6 12. Nh4 $36) 11.
exd4 Nb6 12. Bb3 h6 $6 {Played against Bc1-g5 but the weakness of Black`s
kingside makes possible the following combination.} ({Was safer} 12... Nbd5 13.
Bg5 h6 ({or} 13... Be6) 14. Bh4 Be6 $132 {1/2 Moranda,W (2536)-Sveshnikov,V 
(2386)/ Warsaw 2008(49)}) 13. Bxh6 $5 {A sacrifice without risk because White
has at least a forced draw but Black must find the correct defence.} gxh6 14.
Qg6+ Kh8 15. Qxh6+ Nh7 ({Worse is} 15... Kg8 $6 16. Ng5 Bf5 17. Nxf7 Rxf7 18.
Qg5+ Kf8 19. Bxf7 Kxf7 (19... Bd3 20. Rfd1 Bc2 21. Be6 $5 Bxd1 22. Rxd1 $16)
20. Qxf5 $16) 16. Ne4 Be7 {Black has probably calculated only until this
moment, but White has a possibility to continue the attack.} ({Bad is} 16... f6
$2 17. Nxd6 Qxd6 18. Bc2 Rf7 19. Ng5 $1 Qf8 20. Nxf7+ Qxf7 21. Bxh7 Qxh7 22.
Qxf6+ Qg7 23. Qd8+ Kh7 (23... Qg8 24. Qd6) 24. Rae1 Nd5 25. Re5 Qf7 26. Qh4+
Kg7 27. Rg5+ {1-0 Korpics,Z (2315)-Bodo,N (2280)/Paks 1995}) 17. Nf6 $1 Bf5 (
17... Bxf6 $4 18. Bc2 $18) 18. Nh5 Bf6 (18... Rg8 $2 19. Ne5 $18) 19. Ng5 $1 ({
After} 19. Nh4 {1-0 Kabatianski,A (2275)-Lentrodt,T (2350)/Munich 1993/(60)
Black parries the threats by} Be4 $1 20. Rfe1 $140 Rg8 $1 21. Bxf7 (21. Rxe4 $2
Bg5) 21... Qf8 22. Qxf8 Rgxf8) 19... Bxd4 20. Nxh7 ({Not} 20. Nxf7+ $6 Rxf7 21.
Bxf7 Qg5 $15) 20... Bxh7 21. Rad1 $1 f5 $2 {This is the decisive mistake.} ({
Also wrong was} 21... c5 $2 22. Rxd4 $1 Qxd4 23. Rd1 Qe5 24. f4 Qe3+ (24...
Qxb2 25. Nf6) 25. Kh1 $18) ({But} 21... Rg8 {allowed Black to defend when
White seems to have only perpetual check after} 22. Bc2 Rg6 23. Bxg6 fxg6 24.
Nf4 Qf6 25. Rxd4 (25. Nxg6+ Kg8 (25... Qxg6 26. Qxg6 Bxf2+ 27. Kxf2 Bxg6 28. g4
$13)) 25... Qxd4 26. Nxg6+ (26. Re1 Qg7 27. Qg5 Nd7 $1 28. Re7 Qf6 29. Qh6 $1
Nf8 30. Rxb7 Kg8 31. Nh5 Qe5 32. Rg7+ Kh8 33. Rf7 gxh5 34. Rxf8+ Rxf8 35. Qxf8+
Bg8 36. Qh6+ $11) 26... Kg8 27. Ne7+ Kh8) 22. Rfe1 $1 $18 {And suddenly Black
is helpless against the threat of Rxd4 with Re7 to follow.} Qf6 (22... Nd5 23.
Rxd4 Rf7 24. Qd2 $18) 23. Nxf6 Bxf6 24. Re6 Bg7 25. Qh5 a5 26. Rdd6 Rac8 27.
Re7 a4 28. Rh6 1-0

