{I am showing you this game just to warm you up and introduce an interesting
tactical idea.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 a6 5. Bxc4 b5 $5 {This
move has often been employed by Adianto.} 6. Bd3 Bb7 7. O-O e6 8. a4 b4 9. Nbd2
Nbd7 10. Nb3 c5 11. dxc5 $6 {This exchange assists Black.} (11. Qe2 $142) 11...
Nxc5 12. Nxc5 Bxc5 13. Qc2 $6 (13. b3 $142 O-O 14. Bb2) 13... Rc8 14. Qe2 Qb6 (
14... a5 $5 15. e4 h6 16. Bb5+ Kf8 17. e5 Nd5 {was also possible.}) 15. e4 h6 {
Black prevents Bc1-g5.} 16. a5 Qa7 17. Nd2 $6 {A dubious idea.} ({Correct was} 
17. Bf4) 17... Qa8 $5 (17... O-O) 18. Kh1 (18. e5 Nd7 19. Nf3 O-O $132 (19...
Be7)) 18... h5 $5 {Black is playing for an attack.} 19. f3 h4 {With the
obvious threat of Nh5-g3+.} 20. Nc4 $4 {This natural move loses immediately.} (
{The only defence was} 20. Rd1 Nh5 21. Nf1) 20... Nh5 21. Be3 Ng3+ $1 22. hxg3
hxg3+ 23. Kg1 Ke7 $1 {Preparing the sacrifice of both rooks with a mate to
follow.} 24. Qe1 Rh1+ $1 (24... Rh1+ $1 25. Kxh1 Rh8+ 26. Kg1 Rh1+ $1 27. Kxh1
Qh8+ 28. Kg1 Qh2#) 0-1

