{Another win of Levon Aronian in this variation} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e3 e5
4. Bxc4 Nc6 5. Nf3 e4 6. Nfd2 f5 (6... Qg5 $5 {This is the best move according
to theory.}) 7. O-O Bd6 8. Bxg8 $6 {With this move starts White's problems} (8.
Nc3 Qh4 (8... Nf6 9. f3 exf3 10. Nxf3 $16) 9. g3 Qh3 10. f3 Bxg3 11. Qe2 $16)
8... Rxg8 9. Qh5+ (9. Nc3 Nb4 {[%cal Rb4d3]} 10. f3 $2 (10. Qb3 {The engines
give White a slight preference, but with a human eye, I can't see why White
should be better here.}) 10... Qh4 $1 $17) 9... g6 10. Qxh7 $2 {The final
mistake} Be6 11. Nc3 Qf6 $19 12. d5 O-O-O {White's queen is trapped and it is
game over} 13. f4 Rh8 14. Ndxe4 fxe4 15. Nxe4 Qf8 {Later Aronian converts his
big advantage.} 16. Qxg6 Bxd5 17. Qg4+ Kb8 18. Ng5 Bc5 19. Kh1 Ne5 20. Qg3 Nf7
21. Bd2 Nxg5 22. fxg5 Qe8 23. e4 Bxe4 24. Bf4 Qd7 25. Rae1 Bc6 26. g6 Rdg8 27.
Be5 Bd6 28. Bxd6 Qxd6 29. Qxd6 cxd6 30. Rf6 Rh5 31. Rxd6 Rg5 32. Re2 Kc7 33.
Rf6 R5xg6 34. Rxg6 Rxg6 35. h3 Kd6 36. Kh2 Re6 37. Rd2+ Ke5 38. g4 Kf4 39. Rd4+
Re4 40. Rd2 Re1 0-1

