Bb4 9. Bd2 {this is White's most natural response and the one Black is hoping
for. White's pieces now occupy passive positions and Black does not need to
worry about the possibility of a kingside attack} Nb6 10. Be2 O-O (10... Bb7
11. bxa6 Rxa6 12. Rxa6 Nxa6 13. O-O O-O {simply transposes}) 11. O-O Bb7 12.
bxa6 Rxa6 13. Rxa6 Nxa6 14. Be3 c5 $1 {Once again we encounter this key pawn
