threatening ... Nd3. In many lines, the e5-pawn would be vulnerable.}) 16...
Rxd8 17. Rd1 Rxd1+ 18. Nxd1 Nd7 19. Bxc4 Bxe3 20. Nxe3 Nc7 21. Nd2 Nxe5 $11) ({
The move} 15. Qc1 $6 {is basically losing a pawn after} Bxf3 16. Bxf3 cxd4 17.
Rd1 Bxc3 (17... d3 18. Ne4 $132) 18. bxc3 d3 $17) 15... Bd5 16. Nd6 {White's
knight looks great on d6, but Black can pivot around it quite easily} (16. Qc2
cxd4 17. Nfxd4 Nc5 $15) 16... f6 17. dxc5 (17. b3 $6 cxb3 $1 18. Bxa6 c4 $44 {
[%csl Gb3,Gc4]}) (17. Bd2 $2 cxd4 18. Bxb4 Nxb4 19. Qxd4 Nc6 20. Qe3 Nxe5 $17)
17... Bxc5 $1 $146 (17... Nxc5 $6 18. Nd2 (18. Qc2 $5) 18... fxe5 19. N6xc4
