1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 e5 4. Nf3 exd4 5. Bxc4 Bb4+ 6. Nbd2 Nc6 7. O-O Nf6 (
7... Be6 $6 {This move exists and was popular 20 years ago, but now the theory
considers it dubious.}) 8. e5 Nd5 9. Nb3 Nb6 10. Bb5 Bd7 11. Bg5 Be7 12. Bxc6
Bxc6 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Nfxd4 Bd5 {I spent many hours analyzing this position.
My conclusion is that the position is fine, probably equal, but very tough to
play for Black. One important rule here is that Black should not be in a hurry
to castle. He should keep his options to play 0-0 or 0-0-0.} 15. Qg4 g6 (15...
h5 $1 16. Qxg7 (16. Qh3 $2 g6 $5 (16... O-O $2 17. Qxh5 $6 (17. f4 $1) 17... g6
18. Qg4 Qxe5) 17. f4 a5 $1 $11 {Black has a counterplay connected with a5-a4
and Qb4}) 16... O-O-O 17. Nf5 Qd7 18. Qf6 Bxg2 19. Nc5 (19. Kxg2 Nd5) (19. Ne7+
Kb8 20. Kxg2 Rhe8 21. Nf5 Nd5 22. Qg5 Rxe5) 19... Qb5 20. Rfc1 Rhg8 21. Ng3 Bd5
{Tabatabaei-Xiong,2019}) 16. Rac1 {with the idea to stop c7-c5.} O-O $6 {
as we mentioned, 0-0 is not very accurate} (16... h5 $5 17. Qh3) (16... Bxb3
17. axb3 (17. Nxb3 O-O 18. Qg3 c6 (18... Nd5 19. Nc5 b6 20. Ne4 f5) 19. Nc5 Nd5
) 17... c6 18. f4 Nd5 (18... O-O)) 17. Rfe1 h5 (17... Bxb3 18. Nxb3 Rad8 19. f4
Rd5) (17... f5) 18. Qf4 Nc4 19. Nf5 gxf5 20. Nd4 f6 21. Nxf5 $16 Qh7 22. exf6
Kh8 23. f7 Qxf7 24. Qd4+ Qf6 25. Qxd5 Nxb2 26. Ng3 Qxf2+ 27. Kh1 Qf7 28. Qe5+
Qg7 29. Qxh5+ Qh7 30. Qe5+ Qg7 31. Rxc7 Qxe5 32. Rxe5 Rac8 33. Rec5 Rxc7 34.
Rxc7 Rd8 35. h3 Rd1+ 36. Kh2 Kg8 37. Rxb7 Rd2 38. Rxa7 Nd1 39. Nf5 Rf2 40. Nh6+
Kh8 41. Ng4 Rf4 42. a4 Nc3 43. a5 1-0

