1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 e5 4. Nf3 exd4 5. Bxc4 Bb4+ 6. Nbd2 Nc6 7. O-O Nf6 8.
e5 Nd5 9. Nb3 Nb6 10. Bb5 Bd7 11. Bxc6 $6 (11. Bg5 $5 {only this move can
create problems for Black} Be7 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Re1 (13. Rc1 {Is an
interesting try. I think Black is fine after:} O-O-O 14. Re1 d3) (13. Bxc6 {
This is the main move, which was analyzed before} Bxc6 14. Nfxd4) 13... O-O-O (
13... O-O 14. Rc1 Rad8) 14. Rc1 Nb4 15. Bxd7+ Rxd7 16. Nfxd4 $1 (16. a3 Nc6 17.
Rxc6 bxc6 18. Nfxd4 c5 19. Nc6 Qe6 {and this should be holdable}) 16... Nxa2
17. Ra1 Nb4 18. Qg4 h5 {with a very sharp game}) 11... Bxc6 12. Nfxd4 Bd5 13.
Qg4 (13. Nf5 g6 14. Ng7+ Kf8 15. Bh6 Kg8 16. Nh5 (16. Qg4 Bf8 17. Nf5 Be6 18.
Nbd4 Bxf5 19. Nxf5 Qc8 20. Bxf8 Kxf8 21. Nh6 Qxg4 22. Nxg4 $11) 16... gxh5 17.
Qxh5 f5 18. Qxf5 Qe8 19. f4 Qe6 20. Qh5 Bf8 21. Bxf8 Rxf8 {White has
compensation, but not more than that,}) 13... Qd7 14. e6 fxe6 15. Nxe6 Qxe6 16.
Qxb4 O-O-O 17. Nc5 Qg6 18. f3 Rhf8 19. Qc3 Rf5 20. b4 Nc4 21. Kh1 Re8 22. Bb2
b6 23. Ne4 Rxe4 24. fxe4 Bxe4 25. Rg1 Rh5 26. Bc1 Qg4 27. a4 Qh4 0-1

