1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 Nf6 {I suggest this line, because it is very easy to
play for Black. Probably Black didn't equalize completely, but he has a very
easy play and does not need to remember many things.} 4. Nc3 e5 5. Nf3 (5. d5 {
Usually, this advance is not very good due to:} b5 6. Qc2 (6. Nxb5 Nxe4 7. Qa4
c6 8. dxc6 Nxc6 9. Nc3 Nxc3 10. bxc3 Bd7 {1/2 (47)-1/2 (47) Herraiz Lopez,H  
(2415)-Mellado Trivino,J (2463) Barcelona ESP 2000 The Week in Chess 301 [Mark
Crowther]}) 6... Bb4 7. a4 c6 8. Bg5 O-O 9. Nf3 Qd6 10. Nd2 a6 {1/2 (46)-1/2  
(46) Fajman,P (2203)-Vaculik,M (2293) Czech Republic CZE 2016}) (5. dxe5 Qxd1+
6. Nxd1 (6. Kxd1 Ng4 {0-1 (36) Manojlovic,N (2042) -Raetsky,A (2417) Geneve
SUI 2007 The Week in Chess 638 [Mark Crowther]}) 6... Nxe4 7. Bxc4 Nc6 8. Bd5
Nc5 9. Nf3 Nd3+ {1/2 (30)-1/2 (30) Dietmayer Kraeutler,M (2311)-Kuba,G (2413)
Tweng AUT 2007 The Week in Chess 667 [Mark Crowther]}) 5... exd4 6. Qxd4 Qxd4
7. Nxd4 Bc5 8. Ndb5 {all these endgames are in Black's favor. Do not trust
engines if they say otherwise.} Na6 9. Bf4 c6 10. Nd6+ Bxd6 11. Bxd6 Be6 12. e5
(12. O-O-O O-O-O 13. f4 Ne8 14. Be5 Rxd1+ 15. Nxd1 f6 16. Bd4 Nd6 17. Nf2 Nb5
18. Be3 Rd8 19. f5 Bf7 20. g4 Nd4 21. g5 Nb4 22. Bxd4 Rxd4 23. a3 Na6 24. gxf6
gxf6 25. Kc2 Nc7 26. Rg1 Ne8 27. Rg3 b5 28. Rh3 h5 29. Be2 Nd6 30. Bxh5 Bxh5
31. Rxh5 Nxe4 32. Nxe4 Rxe4 33. Rh6 Re2+ 34. Kc3 Kc7 35. h4 Re3+ 36. Kc2 Rh3
37. h5 a5 38. Rxf6 Rxh5 39. Rf8 Rh2+ 40. Kc1 Kd6 41. f6 Rf2 42. f7 Kc5 43. Ra8
Rxf7 44. Rxa5 Kd4 45. Ra6 Kd3 46. Kb1 Rf1+ 47. Ka2 Kc2 48. Rxc6 Rb1 49. Rh6
Rxb2+ 50. Ka1 c3 51. Rh5 b4 52. axb4 Kb3 {0-1 (52) Ilincic,Z (2430)-Fodor,T  
(2445) Kecskemet HUN 2014 The Week in Chess 1012 [Mark Crowther]}) 12... Nd7
13. Be2 (13. f4 Nac5 14. Be2 b5 15. O-O Nb7 16. Rad1 O-O-O 17. a4 Nb6 18. axb5
Nxd6 19. exd6 Bd5 20. bxc6 Bxc6 21. Rd4 f5 22. Rfd1 Kd7 23. Ra1 Ra8 24. Ra5
Rhf8 25. g4 Rf6 26. Rxf5 Rxf5 27. gxf5 Rf8 28. Bg4 Rf6 29. Kf2 Bh1 30. Ne2 Bd5
31. Ng3 Kc6 32. Nh5 Rf7 33. f6 g6 34. Ng7 Kxd6 35. Be6 Rxf6 36. Bxd5 Kc5 37.
Re4 Nxd5 38. Kg3 Kb4 39. Ne6 a5 40. Nd4 Kc5 41. Ne6+ Kb4 42. Nd4 a4 43. Re5 Rd6
44. Kf3 c3 45. bxc3+ Nxc3 46. Ke3 a3 47. Nc2+ Kb3 48. Nxa3 Kxa3 49. f5 Kb4 50.
