1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 b5 {This line is very fashionable and If you a sharp
player you should choose this line. You sacrifice a material and play for
compensation.} 4. a4 c6 5. axb5 cxb5 6. Nc3 a6 (6... Qb6 {This is the new main
line here. It is very sharp as well. I am giving you some directions to
analyze.} 7. Nd5 (7. b3 e6 8. bxc4 Bb4 9. Qb3 (9. Bd2 bxc4 10. Bxc4 Ne7) 9...
bxc4 10. Bxc4 Nc6 11. Nge2 Na5 12. Qa2 Nxc4 13. Qxc4 a5 $11 {[%cal Rc8a6]})
7... Qb7 8. Bf4 e5 9. Bxe5 Nd7 10. Bf4 Ngf6 11. Nc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8 Qxe4+ 13. Ne2
Qxa8 14. Qd2 (14. f3 Nd5 15. Bg5+ f6 16. Bd2 Bd6 17. Ng3 Qb8 18. Kf2 Re8 19.
Be2 Bc7 20. Re1 {[%cal Rg7g6,Rh7h5,Rh5h4] Later Black can push the h-pawn
Aronian-Dominguez,2022}) 14... Nd5 {[%csl Rd5,Rd7] Black king feels safe in
the middle of the board. The d4-pawn is a potential weakness in the future} 15.
Nc3 Bb4 16. Be2 Re8 17. Bg3 N7f6 18. O-O Ne4 {Aronian-Nakamura 2022}) 7. Nxb5
axb5 8. Rxa8 Bb7 {I analyze this position in great depth. I am giving you all
my analyses which I think are pretty good.} 9. Ra2 $1 {This is a very
difficult move and the only move to fight for the advantage.} (9. Ra1 e6 10.
Nf3 (10. Ne2 Bxe4 11. b3 (11. Nc3 $1 Bc6 $1 (11... Bb4 12. Be2 Bxg2 (12... Ne7
13. O-O Bc6 14. Bf3 O-O 15. Bxc6 Nbxc6 16. Nxb5 Qb6 17. Na3 Na5) 13. Rg1 Bc6
14. Rxg7 Ne7 15. Kf1 Nf5 16. Rg4) 12. Be2 b4 13. Nb1 Bxg2 14. Rg1 Bd5 (14...
Bc6 $1 15. Nd2 (15. Bxc4 Ne7) 15... c3 16. bxc3 bxc3 17. Nf3 Ne7 18. Qb3 (18.
