Therefore, Black's idea is to take control over the g3-square first and only
then break on f6} 12. Rc1 (12. Bc2 h4 {Black is proceeding with his plan} 13.
h3 Be7 14. b4 g5 15. Be4 Kb8 16. f3 (16. Rc1 g4 $40) 16... f6 $13) (12. Qc1 h4
13. Rd1 (13. h3 Kb8 {is a lot like the main line}) 13... Qe8 (13... h3 $5 {
is possible too}) 14. Bc2 Bxc2 15. Qxc2 f6 16. exf6 gxf6 17. h3 Kb8 18. b4 Bd6
19. Kh1 Qf7 20. Rac1 Rhg8 $15 {Black has a better game in Izoria, Z (2450)
-Ganguly,S (2498), Yerevan 2000}) (12. Ng3 {is just bad for White} Bg6 13. Nge4
h4 14. h3 Nxd4 $17) (12. Ba2 {doesn't make so much sense} h4 13. b4 (13. h3 f6
14. exf6 (14. b4 Kb8 15. Qc1 Qe8 16. f4 Qg6 17. Kh1) 14... gxf6 15. Nf4 Bh6 $17
) 13... f6 (13... h3 $5 14. g3 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Qc6 $19) 14. exf6 gxf6 15. Nf4 Bh6
16. d5 Bxf4 17. Bxf4 exd5 18. Rc1 Ne5 19. Qd4 Bh3 20. f3 Rhg8 21. Rc2 Qf5 22.
Re2 {Kasimdzhanov,R (2603)-Jonkman,H (2421) Wijk aan Zee 1999} Bxg2 $1 23. Rxg2
Rxg2+ 24. Kxg2 Rg8+ 25. Kh1 (25. Kf2 Nd3+ 26. Ke3 Nxf4 27. Qxf4 Re8+ $19) 25...
Qh3 26. Rf2 Nxf3 $19) 12... h4 13. h3 f6 14. Na4 (14. exf6 $6 {this capture
usually leads to trouble for White} gxf6 15. d5 (15. Nf4 Bh6 16. d5 Qg7 $17)
15... Nxd5 16. Nxd5 exd5 $17) 14... Nd5 15. Nc5 Bxc5 16. Rxc5 {Van Hoolandt,P 
